This topic describes how to use DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta).

You can create service instances of DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) and bind them to apps using the Cloud Foundry Command-Line Interface (cf CLI).

Download an example app that uses DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) <a href="https://github.com/mp911de/spring-music/tree/cassandra">here</a>.

##<a id='using'></a> Create a Service Instance

Creating a service instance in PCF automatically does the following:

  * Spins up a dedicated DataStax Enterprise cluster based on the user-selected service plan.
  * Creates a DataStax Enterprise OpsCenter instance to manage the DataStax Enterprise cluster.
  * Generates an associated user account in the DataStax Enterprise cluster to let the instance access the cluster. 

The following procedures describe how to create a DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) service instance with the cf CLI.

1. Run `cf marketplace -s p-dse-cassandra-v1` to view the available service plans:
![dse-cassandra in cf marketplace](cf_marketplace.png)
 
1. Run `cf create-service SERVICE-NAME SERVICE-PLAN SERVICE-INSTANCE-NAME -c '{"cluster_size" : n}` to create a service instance where:
  * The `-c` option defines the cluster size. If you skip the `-c` option, the service instance defaults as follows:
      - A 3-node DataStax Enterprise cluster for the `sample-bronze-plan` or  `sample-silver-plan`
      - A 5-node DataStax Enterprise cluster for the `sample-gold-plan`
  * `SERVICE-INSTANCE-NAME` can be any descriptive name you want to use for the service instance.
  ![ALT-TEXT](cf_create_service.png)

##<a id='using'></a> Bind an App to a Service Instance

To bind a DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) service instance to a PCF app using the cf CLI:

1. Run `cf service SERVICE-INSTANCE-NAME` to view your service instance:  
![cf service dse-cassandra-instance](cf_service_dse.png)

1. Run `cf bind-service APP-NAME SERVICE-INSTANCE-NAME` to bind the app to the service instance:  
![cf bind-service](cf_bind_service_dse.png)

1. Run `cf restage APP-NAME` to restage your app:  
![cf restage](cf_restage_app.png)

##<a id='using'></a> Access the DataStax Enterprise OpsCenter

To access the OpsCenter dashboard for a DataStax Enterprise for PCF service instance:

1. Run `cf env APP-NAME` to show all environment variables for an app: 
![cf env](cf_env_opsc_creds.png)<br>

1. Browse to the OpsCenter's login URL listed as `opscenter_url` in the output from `cf env`. For example, `datastax-opscenter-40843970-e3a5-41c3-bc14-71ce04a00339.sys.pie-88.com/opscenter/login.html`.

1. Log into the OpsCenter dashboard using the `opscenter_admin_username` and `opscenter_admin_password` values listed in the `cf env` output.
![DataStax OpsCenter dashboard](opsc_dashboard.png)

##<a id='using'></a> Delete a Service Instance

Run `cf delete-service SERVICE-INSTANCE-NAME` to delete an instance of the DataStax Enterprise for PCF (Beta) service.

When you delete a service instance, the broker automatically unbinds all apps that are bound to that service and de-provisions the DataStax Enterprise cluster associated with the service instance.
